  "texts": [
    "For example, the track field's length is crucial for the evaluation since different runners can perform differently if the 'rules of the game' are modified.",
    "The conditions of the race affect the runners' performance, which is equivalent to saying that generative models are affected by factors such as the type and size of the dataset, the ground truth distribution to be learned, etc.",
    "Each instance of a generative modeling task is unique, just as the conditions for every day of the competitions could be unique.",
    "As such, the tracks and the race conditions must be specified before the competition happens, to clarify the precise setting where the search for PQA (or, in our study, for PPQA) takes place.",
    "Lastly, we argue that, when evaluating performance in a concrete instance of a race on a given track, the measure of success for an athlete might not necessarily be attributed to the maximum speed."
